{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1a39a0c-1ead-4e00-9a30-be3bd99e6e92","content":"The directory is empty — no existing files to convert. Here's exactly how to do it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage\n\n```xml\n<!-- SettingsPage.xaml -->\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             Title=\"Settings\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme name\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe only structural change is:\n- Add the `xmlns:vm` namespace import\n- Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage`\n\nThis tells the XAML compiler to resolve all `{Binding …}` paths against `SettingsViewModel` at compile time. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat XAML binding warnings (XC00XX) as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045;XC0022;XC0023</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the declared `x:DataType` |\n| `XC0022` | No matching property/method for binding path |\n| `XC0023` | Type mismatch in binding |\n\n### 3. Opting out for dynamic sections\n\nIf part of the page binds to a different or unknown type, locally disable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<StackLayout x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\">\n    <!-- back to runtime-resolved bindings here -->\n    <Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" />\n</StackLayout>\n```\n\n**In short:** add `x:DataType` → bindings resolve at compile time → enable `WarningsAsErrors` for the `XC00XX` codes → typos and type mismatches break the build instead of failing silently.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"358fba85-2684-4f8a-a287-fd41a224e11a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there are no files. The user is asking me to help them convert a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. Since there are no actual files, I'll provide the guidance directly.\n\nLet me give them a concrete example showing the before/after conversion and explain how to catch binding errors at build time.","outputTokens":761},"id":"bc6d0764-dc2f-453c-a559-16878fc2cde1","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:59:25.491Z","parentId":"5fff7f97-fed4-4616-a106-7ee8f5fa51e3"}
